headline.main: LONG ISLAND.; Excitement in the City of Charelies--A Circus Deciuted Dangerous to the Health of the City.

THE JOSEPH WALKER CASE.; RESUMPTION OF TESTIMONY. Mr. Walter R. Jones is Recalled, and makes Certain curious Statements about the Interference of Alderman Moser, Alderman Herrick, and Mr. George H. Covert. FUN ALL ROUND!

docs.lead_paragraph: The Special Committee on the Joseph Walker business met this afternoon at 3 o'clock. TESTIMONY OF ISAAC O. BARKER. The first witness called was Isaac O. headline.main: FROM WASHINGTON.; Mr. Secretary Marey--The Administration and the Hard. Shells--Affairs of Kansas.

docs.lead_paragraph: The weather continues to threaten dissolution. Mr. MARCY has acknowledged its centrifugal influence and gone away Southward, to avoid the heat and sniff the breezes which come up fresh from the sea to where POWHATAN reigned and POCAHONTAS loved.
